File: Chad le Clos has taken a voluntary 65 percent salary cut as the virus keeps live sport on hold globally. JOHANNESBURG - South African swimming star Chad le Clos has taken a salary cut to help struggling swimmers during the ongoing coronavirus pandemic. Le Clos has taken a voluntary 65 percent salary cut as the virus keeps live sport on hold globally. Reports suggest that his CLeC Academy was forced to close due to the coronavirus. READ: Le Clos faces uncertain training future amid Olympic doubts However, the foundation is still going strong helping those less fortunate follow their dreams. All sport in South Africa has been suspended since 19 March. Despite South Africa moving to Level 4 of the lockdown, there will be no resumption of sport.